CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 7, 1957, pg. B2, reads: "Bound fro Lott-Carey Convention - The young people of the Allegheny Union Baptist Association pose for The Courier photographer just before the bus, which the group sponsored took them to Orange, N.J. for the Lott - Carey convention, Aug. 26-30. Mrs. West and several other adults went along to supervise the young members. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women, men, and girls from Allegheny Union Baptist Association, gathered with suitcases and luggage before bus trip to Lott Carey convention in Orange, New Jersey
